    {
      "id": "dmf-pattern",
      "type": "markdown",
      "label": "Two-Agent Pattern",
      "position": {
        "x": -40,
        "y": 220
      },
      "width": 660,
      "height": 300,
      "visible": true,
      "showLabel": true,
      "data": {
        "markdown": "## Two-Agent Pattern (Initializer → Worker)\nNot about personalities — about who owns memory.\n\n- **Initializer:** expands the prompt into memory artifacts (feature list, rules, scaffolding)\n- **Worker:** reads memory, picks one item, makes small testable progress, updates memory, commits, exits\n\nEvery run starts the same way: **read memory → verify state → act**.",
        "_classBinding": {
          "key": "markdown",
          "sourceRef": "/library/classes/nodes/markdown.node-class.node",
          "ref": "/library/classes/nodes/markdown.node-class.node",
          "identity": {
            "graphId": "markdown_class",
            "name": "markdown Node Class",
            "version": "0.1.0",
            "description": "Canonical markdown content node.",
            "createdAt": "2026-02-24T20:05:15Z",
            "updatedAt": "2026-03-24T01:20:00.000Z"
          },
          "intent": "graph",
          "meaning": "Canonical markdown content node.",
